My thoughts on 

roe vs wade 
Pro life vs pro choice 

I have seen that, in my genuine attempts to understand, open minded people are the ones that listen to my logic and also share their logic. They go beyond the reactionary emotions that come up on vehement disagreement on the other's logic. 

I genuinely believe We are all trying to understand thr truth and some are at different levels and are tying to help each other.

Won't entertain anyone who isn't 
aligned with that :)

#roevswade #prolife #prochoice #redvsblue #truth

“The Convenience trap”

What are we doing to protect ourselves from it?

#yoga #yogapractice #convenience #trap #motivation #drive #inspiration

Have you ever pondered how do I not waste time in thinking unnecessary things?
Or have you wondered how to just enjoy simple things?

Its not the answers but the quality of questions that shape our lives.

We are bunch of like minded people that get together over zoom every week and ask the tough questions. 

Questions asked in right environment or to right teacher.. Or sometimes to the universe will give a much deeper answer.

Questions like 
How do I (as an individual) beat the system that designs systems to keep me addicted to technology / screen?

What are my additions and how do I overcome them?

How do I get the TRUE news? What is the framework with which I can approach that? Does it change with time?

ETC.

You can come join on weekly masterminds with us and be a part of these discussions. 

No. Its not free. Its a paid thing.

Its happening on Sundays 9.30 to 11am IST (December).
From Jan onwards it will shift back to Saturdays 9 to 10.30am IST.

#mastermind #lifecoaching #tribe #levelup

When Shilpa joined last year in June 2020 (online classes), she couldn't even do Sirsasana without wall and also 1 minute chakrasanas were a challenge. Now not only has she mastered that and various variations of it, but she has come a long way to be able to do Natarajasana! And has also become a yoga teacher now inspiring and guiding others!

Truly amazing and inspiring

#yoga #online #onlineclasses #onlineyoga #onlineyogaclasses #zoomyoga #natarajasana #backbends

latestIgtvVideos.title: The invitation by oriah
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
The Invitation by Oriah

It doesn’t interest me
what you do for a living.
I want to know
what you ache for
and if you dare to dream
of meeting your heart’s longing.

It doesn’t interest me
how old you are.
I want to know 
if you will risk 
looking like a fool
for love
for your dream
for the adventure of being alive.

It doesn’t interest me
what planets are 
squaring your moon...
I want to know
if you have touched
the centre of your own sorrow
if you have been opened
by life’s betrayals
or have become shrivelled and closed
from fear of further pain.

I want to know
if you can sit with pain
mine or your own
without moving to hide it
or fade it
or fix it.
I want to know
if you can be with joy
mine or your own
if you can dance with wildness
and let the ecstasy fill you 
to the tips of your fingers and toes
without cautioning us
to be careful
to be realistic
to remember the limitations
of being human.

It doesn’t interest me
if the story you are telling me
is true.
I want to know if you can
disappoint another
to be true to yourself.
If you can bear
the accusation of betrayal
and not betray your own soul.
If you can be faithless
and therefore trustworthy.
I want to know if you can see Beauty
even when it is not pretty
every day.
And if you can source your own life
from its presence.

I want to know
if you can live with failure
yours and mine
and still stand at the edge of the lake
and shout to the silver of the full moon,
“Yes.”

It doesn’t interest me
to know where you live
or how much money you have.
I want to know if you can get up
after the night of grief and despair
weary and bruised to the bone
and do what needs to be done
to feed the children.

It doesn’t interest me
who you know
or how you came to be here.
I want to know if you will stand
in the centre of the fire
with me
and not shrink back.

It doesn’t interest me
where or what or with whom
you have studied.
I want to know 
what sustains you
from the inside
when all else falls away.
I want to know
if you can be alone 
with yourself
and if you truly like
the company you keep
in the empty moments.

latestPosts.caption:
Yoga is an art of precision! 🧘‍♂️

Sometimes, the smallest of things that you often neglect makes a huge difference.

Like, in the case of many people doing kapotasana or raj kapotasana. People often wonder that why they are unable to do the asana correctly despite of trying everything. What they usually ignore is there hand placements. Even when their legs and body are in correct posture, they still fail because of just hand placements.

This is why one should always focus on each and every detail while trying an asana.

6 things people often get wrong about Sattvik diet. Lets not complicate things. here's simple pointers:

1. Focus on whole, fresh, natural foods.

2. Include high amounts of protein in each meal

3. Opt for local & seasonfal food

4. Ghee, Greek yogurt, curd, paneer, milk are your friends

5. Eat mindfully. While eating, just eat.

6. Don't overstimulate your tastebuds with spices all the time.

Share this to increase awareness.

Usually, mayurasana is done with fingers pointed backwards. This is a small variation, and this is not that easy either. 

Many times, this is used in Ashtanga Vinasa primary series as a way to transitioning from Padmasana. The Lotus pose to downward facing dog .

Progress in postures like Mayurasana doesn’t come from force. It comes from consistent practice, compassionate self-awareness, and the willingness to learn from the little things.
